flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn case-intent truth into operational case truth"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than trigger selection and narrower than label truth"]
    G3["Answer how the platform creates a real case and an append-only operational timeline that later operators, auditors, and downstream supervision can trust"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw RTDL output anymore and it is not generic operational noise"]
    E2["The entry is case-intent truth already produced by the case-trigger surface and handed off through the case-trigger boundary"]
    E3["The production paths doc splits the case-escalation path into RTDL decision/audit outputs, case-trigger surface, case creation, and case timeline updates"]
    E4["The topic contract pins the case-trigger topic with case-trigger as producer and case management as consumer"]
    E5["So the input to case management is an explicit case-intent handoff rather than an inferred side effect"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Case-intent truth"]
    R2["Case-management intake"]
    R3["Deterministic case creation"]
    R4["Append-only timeline writes"]
    R5["Operational case truth"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Case-intent truth from the upstream trigger boundary"]
    C2["Enough incident identity to make case identity deterministic"]
    C3["Run and upstream decision continuity"]
    C4["Timeline events and transition facts"]
    C5["Evidence needed to reconstruct why the case exists and how it evolved"]
    C6["The platform expects to observe case-open counts, case-transition counts, timeline events/appends, duplicate case-creation anomalies, invalid case-state transitions, and run-scope continuity into case outputs"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats operational case truth as its own append-only truth system"]
    L2["It is not a mutable convenience view and not a precursor storage area for labels"]
    L3["There is a dedicated boundary where case identity becomes real"]
    L4["The operational case history is written append-only, auditable, and reconstructable"]
    L5["That is why case management is defined around append-only timeline integrity, duplicate-case-creation at zero, invalid-transition rate at zero, and case reconstruction completeness rather than a generic case-service-up story"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The copied baseline wired graphs show a live case-management deployment in the case-and-label namespace"]
    S2["The case-trigger topic feeds case management"]
    S3["Case management writes append-only case timeline truth into Aurora"]
    S4["So operational case truth is seated on concrete workload plus relational truth substrate rather than inside ephemeral stream logic"]
    S5["The platform already treats case management as a concrete observable boundary through case-open success rate, duplicate case-creation count, append-only timeline violations, invalid case-state transition count, and case reconstruction completeness"]
    S6["Later timing work identified the actual processing clocks as case-trigger intake first-seen time and case-created time, showing these are authoritative case-open timing surfaces rather than rough event-time proxies"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform does not want operational truth to be mutable, duplicated, or collapsed into label truth"]
    Y2["That is why case management is explicitly defined around deterministic case identity, idempotent case creation, append-only timeline transitions, zero hidden overwrite corruption, reconstruction after the fact, and non-ownership of label truth"]
    Y3["The later proving notes around timing reinforce the same design intent"]
    Y4["They show that the platform had to distinguish true case-management processing clocks from earlier misleading event-oriented timestamps"]
    Y5["That only matters in a system where case creation and timeline append are treated as real operational truth boundaries rather than loose workflow artifacts"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The Case + Label plane contract shapes what case management is allowed to mean: semantic correctness, ownership correctness, duplicate and replay safety, latency and throughput, and auditability"]
    X2["The whole-plane truth-ownership contract shapes what case management is not allowed to steal: case-trigger owns trigger selection, case management owns case timeline truth, label store owns label truth"]
    X3["The topic continuity contract shapes the handoff into case management: case-trigger topic, producer = case-trigger surface, consumer = case management"]
    X4["The phase plan and telemetry contract shapes how this path must be judged: duplicate case creation count = 0, case-open success = 100%, append-only timeline violations = 0, case-open latency p95 <= 5 s, invalid state-transition count = 0"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds a stricter truth boundary than a simpler workflow system would"]
    T2["That costs one more owned service/runtime boundary, deterministic case-identity logic, append-only timeline discipline, duplicate suppression, transition validation, and later reconstruction logic"]
    T3["But that cost buys the ability to answer not just that a case exists, but why it exists, when it was opened, how it evolved, whether it was duplicated, and whether the operational history was mutated or appended"]
    T4["That is exactly the kind of operational truth a fraud platform needs if review, audit, and later supervision are to rest on trustworthy operational history rather than mutable snapshots"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still generate case-worthy signals, keep RTDL truth, and eventually write labels somehow"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to where operational case identity comes from"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to whether one incident maps to one case deterministically"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to how case history is preserved and whether duplicate triggers remint case truth"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to how an operator or reviewer reconstructs the operational story later"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the platform would have escalation and labels, but no explicit owner for operational case truth itself"]
    N7["If case timelines are mutable or inconsistent, review and audit are broken"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Deterministic case identity exists"]
    O2["Case creation is idempotent under duplicate triggers"]
    O3["The append-only case timeline is now the authoritative case-truth surface"]
    O4["Owned outcome: deterministic operational case truth plus append-only case history"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning case-intent truth into deterministic operational case truth and append-only case history"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>case management is not a generic workflow bucket; it is explicitly designed around deterministic case identity, idempotent case creation, and append-only timeline ownership"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>this boundary is concretely seated in the case-management workload, the case-trigger handoff, and the Aurora-backed case timeline substrate"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by duplicate-case-creation at zero, append-only timeline integrity, case reconstruction completeness, and strict non-ownership of label truth"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the platform already knows this boundary can fail through duplicate creation, invalid transitions, or misleading timestamp bases, which is why those concerns are surfaced explicitly rather than hidden"]
    A6["Material participation evidence:<br/>the bounded case-and-label closure metrics say the slice closed green with large admitted-request volume, zero 4xx and 5xx, and clean case-trigger, case-management, and label-store integrity deltas"]
    A7["A-level meaning:<br/>case-intent truth becomes deterministic, append-only operational case truth rather than leaving operational review to mutate ad hoc workflow state"]
  end

